  DISEASES & MEDICINE
============================================================

Disease:     Hepatitis B
Type:        Viral
Pathogen:    HBV
Transmission:Blood, sexual contact
Symptoms:    Often asymptomatic; jaundice
Treatment:   Antivirals (tenofovir)
Deaths/yr:   0.82M
Vaccine:     Yes (highly effective)
Discovered:  1965

Disease:     Alzheimer's
Type:        Neurological
Pathogen:    Non-communicable
Transmission:Aging/genetics
Symptoms:    Memory loss, confusion
Treatment:   No cure; slowing medications
Deaths/yr:   0.12M
Vaccine:     No
Discovered:  1906

Disease:     Tuberculosis
Type:        Bacterial
Pathogen:    M. tuberculosis
Transmission:Airborne droplets
Symptoms:    Persistent cough, night sweats
Treatment:   6-9 month antibiotics
Deaths/yr:   1.6M
Vaccine:     Yes (BCG, partial)
Discovered:  1882

